title: Rijksmuseum
description: The Rijksmuseum is the museum of the Netherlands. The completely renovated Rijksmuseum tells the story of the Netherlands from the Middle Ages to the 20th century. Including works by Rembrandt, Vermeer, Frans Hals, and more! Most famous is Rembrandt's masterpiece the Night Watch. A new display of the collection, a renewed building, new public facilities, a revamped garden and a new Asian Pavilion. Open daily from 9 am to 5 pm.

title: Anne Frank House
description: The Anne Frank House (Dutch: Anne Frank Huis) is a museum dedicated to Jewish wartime diarist Anne Frank. The building is located on a canal called the Prinsengracht, close to the Westerkerk, in central Amsterdam in the Netherlands. As a visitor, you experience this story through a audio tour, quotes, photos, videos, and original items. The Anne Frank House can only be visited with an online ticket for a specific date and time.
location: Prinsengracht 263 - 267 museum entrance Westermarkt 20, 1016 DK Amsterdam The Netherlands

title: Van Gogh Museum
description: Discover the world's largest collection of works by Dutch painter Vincent van Gogh, featuring masterpieces such as Sunflowers, The Potato Eaters, Almond Blossom and The Bedroom. Book your tickets online. Please consult the museum website for current opening hours.

title: A'dam Lookout
description: LOOKOUT 360º Amsterdam + sensational swing An iconic viewing point in The Netherlands - A’DAM LOOKOUT, has joined the Eiffel Tower, the Fernsehturm and the London Eye. For the daredevils among us, LOOKOUT also has a further adrenalin kick in store. On the roof is Europe’s highest swing. You swing over the edge of the tower at a thrilling height of almost 100 metres above the ground. Highlights: - The most spectacular view of Amsterdam and the surrounding area - A Bird’s-eye view of Amsterdam from the highest swing in Europe - Access to the indoor interactive state-of-the-art Amsterdam exhibition - Free digital photo of your visit to LOOKOUT - Enjoy coffee, breakfast, lunch, dinner and/or cocktails in Madam Restaurant & Sky Bar - Free WIFI available Payments with cards only.

title: Body Worlds
description: Gunther von Hagens’ BODY WORLDS: The Happiness Project in the heart of Amsterdam tells the amazing story of our own body and the impact of happiness on our health. More than 200 anatomical specimens of real human bodies show the complexity, resilience and vulnerability of the body. Join the 40 million people around the world who have already seen the exhibition and been on this fascinating voyage of discovery through the human body.

title: Royal Palace Amsterdam
description: The Royal Palace Amsterdam is in use by the Dutch Royal House. Most of the year, the Royal Palace is alsof open for visitors. You are welcome to discover the rich history and interior of this magnificent building in the heart of Amsterdam. Visitors are welcome to discover the building's rich past and legacies left by it's successive occupants - as Amsterdam's Town Hall for 150 years, the French Royal and Imperial Palace for 5 years and the Palace of the House of Orange for the past two centuries. The Royal Palace was built in the seventeenth century as the Town Hall of Amsterdam, after a design by Jacob van Campen. It's paintings and sculptures were made by some of the most distinguished artists of the time and allude to the city's influence and prosperity in the Dutch Golden Age. In 1808 Louis Napoleon, brother of the French Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte, became King of Holland and converted the Town Hall into a Palace. The superb collection of Empire furniture, clocks and chandeliers date from that period. The collection of Empire furniture is one of the best preserved and most complete collections in the world. The rooms in the Palace are decorated with artworks from the collection of the House of Orange-Nassau Historic Collections Trust. Many paintings show the various members of the family of Orange-Nassau
location: Nieuwezijds Voorburgwal 147, 1012 RJ Amsterdam The Netherlands

title: Heineken Experience
description: The Heineken Experience is a self guided interactive journey through the world of Heineken(R). You can discover the history of the company, the 4 natural ingredients of our beer, the brewing process, a tasting room and the Heineken(R) brand. At the end of the tour you can enjoy 2 Heinekens(R) or learn how to draught the perfect Heineken(R).

title: Het Scheepvaartmuseum| The National Maritime Museum
description: The National Maritime Museum holds one of the world's largest and most notable maritime collections including paintings, ship models, navigation instruments and sea charts. Discover 500 years of Dutch maritime history and its strong link to society of today and tomorrow.

title: NEMO Science Museum
description: Expand your world at NEMO Science Museum. In the largest science museum of the Netherlands you will find proof that science and technology can be captivating for all ages. The remarkable building on top of the IJ-tunnel offers five floors of exciting hands-on activities. At NEMO you can experience the joy of science and technology, by blowing gigantic soap bubbles, watch an enormous chain reaction and experiment in a real laboratory. In a variety of exhibitions you can 'Take a journey through the mind' or learn that there is more than meets the eye when it comes to sustainable electricity and smart transportation at 'Smart Technology'. Enjoy a magnificent view over Amsterdam The creative mind behind NEMO, build in 1997, is Italian architect Renzo Piano. He had a clear vision for his design of the NEMO building, with its very own piazza 22 metres above water level. The spectacular roof terrace has a magnificent view over Amsterdam and the Eastern Docklands. You can access the roof terrace free of charge. The roof terrace and cafe in NEMO are the perfect places to sit back, relax and enjoy a drink.

Recently, the genuine YAB YUM feeling is brought back to life. YAB YUM Unlocked is a wonderful exhibition and a 'Real Life Club Experience' at the same time. title: Museum De Dageraad
description: Behind the wave-shaped facade of the famous working-class housing complex De Dageraad, you will find information about the art and architecture of the Amsterdam School. At the beginning of the last century, H.P. Berlage designed the now famous Plan Zuid. He introduced a new way of urban planning, in which there was room for wide streets, atmospheric squares and green parks. The characteristic architecture of the many Amsterdam School artists still adorns the street plan. The expressionistic facades and beautiful ornaments are recognizable throughout the neighborhood. Residential complex De Dageraad is the Amsterdam School in its purest form. Architects Michel de Klerk and Piet Kramer were commissioned to design all facets of the streetscape. In addition to the street facades, they also designed the rear facades and floor plans. This led to a form of total art in which beauty was central. Museum De Dageraad is the starting point for many walks and cycling tours in the neighbourhood.

The museum dwelling is an original period apartment completely remodelled in the style of the fifties. The museum organizes guided walks and tours through the outdoor museum, visits to the museum dwelling, and talks, events and educational projects about all kinds of topics related to Van Eesteren, (post-war) urban planning and architecture, and the (Western) Garden Citie(s). title: Moco Museum Tickets
description: The Modern Contemporary (Moco) Museum Amsterdam is housed inside Villa Alsberg, a 1904 townhouse in the middle of Amsterdam Museumplein. High-profile guest curators and exhibitions highlight some of the modern world's best contributors to the art world. Eduard Cuypers, cousin of Rijksmuseum designer Pierre Cuypers, designed the townhouse, making it a sight to see in itself. But the work inside is absolutely phenomenal; two current attractions showcase the work of street art activist Banksy, and pop artist extraordinaire, Andy Warhol.

title: The Upside Down Tickets
description: The Upside Down is the biggest Instagram museum in Europe – but it's more than just a museum. It's part amusement park, part club, part magic mushroom trip! Get your friends together and remember to charge your phones; you'll need battery power for all the photos you'll take in this mind-melting world of fun. Explore the boundaries of your own creativity, trick your brain and tickle your senses.

title: Keukenhof Tickets
description: The tulip is one of the most iconic symbols of the Netherlands – and nowhere are they worshipped more whole-heartedly than at the Keukenhof. Known as the Garden of Europe, Keukenhof has fields of more than seven million tulips spread out over 32 hectares.

title: Heineken Experience Tickets
description: The Heineken Experience is located in the original Heineken Brewery. Gerard Adriaan Heineken bought this building back in 1863 when it was the De Hooiberg brewery. He then turned it towards the production of his eponymous beer. The building remained a brewery all the way up to 1988. It was then that it became a museum (and hotspot for Heineken consumption).

title: NEMO Science Museum Tickets
description: NEMO Science Museum is a science centre in Amsterdam, located at the Oosterdok. It was built on top of the IJ-tunnel that connects the centre of Amsterdam with the north of the city. The striking building, designed by Italian architect and engineer, Renzo Piano, opened its doors in 1997. Some say the shape of the building mimics the appearance of a large boat, but others suggest that it's actually a reflection of the tunnel it was built upon.

title: Madame Tussauds Amsterdam Tickets
description: Madame Tussauds is located in the center of Amsterdam at the ever-busy Dam Square. Founded by wax sculptor Marie Tussaud in the 18th century, this iconic wax museum chain has locations in many cities across the globe, including London, Berlin, New York, Las Vegas, Hong Kong, and Shanghai, and of course, the Dutch capital.

title: XtraCold Icebar Tickets
description: Welcome to the coolest bar in Amsterdam (literally). This teeth-chattering locale is the perfect spot to sample the lifestyle of a Polar explorer, without the risk of frostbite. Just meters from the busy Rembrandt Square, this is a great stop on a night on the town in Amsterdam. Free drinks and thermals should keep you warm. The bar is sculpted from 60 tons of natural ice and even your glass here is made from frozen H2O!

title: Amaze Amsterdam Tickets
description: AMAZE Amsterdam is an immersive experience created by the world's largest dance event organizer ID&T. Visitors experience a journey from head to heart, where they are taken through seven experience worlds filled with state-of-the-art audiovisual technology.

title: ARTIS Amsterdam Royal Zoo Tickets
description: The main purpose of ARTIS, the oldest zoo in the Netherlands, is to stimulate the care and love for nature. There are 27 historical buildings in the 140,000 m2 of the park. It's tucked away in a leafy green part of the city (the 'Plantage' District), and is a lovely place for nature lovers.

title: Stedelijk Museum Amsterdam Tickets
description: The Stedelijk Museum in Amsterdam was founded in 1874 and officially opened its doors in 1895. The building was designed by the architect Adriaan Willem Weissman and is located at the Museum Square, where you can also find The Rijksmuseum and The Van Gogh Museum.

title: Our House Amsterdam Tickets
description: Our House is the world’s first modern museum of electronic music culture!

title: STRAAT Museum Tickets
description: Just a quick ferry ride to NDSM from Amsterdam Central Station, you'll find this warehouse museum that pays tribute to a unique medium: street art. With roughly 150 artworks by 140 artists from 32 nationalities, this is your chance to see some of the best street art from around the world without ever leaving Amsterdam.

title: The Cat Cabinet Tickets
description: The Cat Cabinet (Het KattenKabinet) is puuurrfectly located in the 'Golden Bend' of the Herengracht. Situated on the classically-furnished piano nobile of a storied 17th-century canal house, there are many rooms full of cat paraphernalia (and real cats).

title: Ripley's Believe It or Not! Amsterdam Tickets
description: Located on Amsterdam’s Dam Square, this cabinet of curiosities showcases more than 500 exhibits and artifacts in its five floors. The items, ranging from actual Olympic torches to a very unusual Fabergé egg, are organized in 19 themed galleries. There’s also a spacious café with a view to the square and a 5D cinema on the fourth floor.

title: Amsterdam Light Festival Cruises
description: The Amsterdam Light Festival transforms the city's iconic canals into a sparkling winter playground, filled with illuminated artworks from some of the world's top artists. Of course, the best way to experience the dazzling artistry is from the water, letting you get up close and personal with the best the festival from the UNESCO-protected canal network.

title: Red Light Secrets Tickets
description: The Red Light Secrets, Amsterdam's Museum of Prostitution, is a window into what goes on in the famous (notorious?) Red Light District. Located at Oudezijds Achterburgwal 60H, the museum is just a 5-minute walk from Centraal Station, on one of the picturesque canals that make up the area the locals call 'de Wallen'.

title: Jewish Cultural Quarter Tickets
description: The Jewish Cultural Quarter includes the Jewish Museum (formerly known as the Jewish Historical Museum), the Portuguese Synagogue (built in 1675), the Hollandsche Schouwburg (National Holocaust Memorial), and the Jewish Museum Junior (an educational children's museum designed like a traditional Jewish home).

title: BODY WORLDS: The Happiness Project Tickets
description: The German anatomist Gunther von Hagens, who invented the plastination technique in the late 1970s at teh University of Heidelberg, developed this exhibition.

title: Eye Film Museum Tickets
description: Eye Filmmuseum is the museum for film and the art of the moving image. Located in the iconic building on the IJ River, Eye organizes exhibitions at the intersection of film and visual arts and film programs that shed light on the very earliest film history, to the most current social developments. Eye's collection includes more than 50,000 Dutch and international films and a multitude of posters, photographs, film equipment, books and personal archives, including the renowned Unesco World Heritage Collection of film pioneer Jean Desmet. Eye preserves, restores and presents film; from classics, blockbusters and early avant-garde films to the very latest VR experiments.

title: THIS IS HOLLAND Tickets
description: THIS IS HOLLAND offers a simulated flight experience with a spherical screen and special effects to enhance a state-of-the-art journey over The Netherlands. Visitors will see cultural highlights and landmarks, as well as learn about the history of The Netherlands.

title: Royal Palace Amsterdam (Koninklijk Paleis) Tickets
description: The impressive Royal Palace Amsterdam, located on Dam Square, is one of Amsterdam's top attractions. It was built in the Dutch Golden Age as the city hall for Amsterdam. It later became a palace for the royal family, a function it still has to this day. Consequently, it's not always open to the public.

title: Het Scheepvaartmuseum (National Maritime Museum) Tickets
description: Het Scheepvaartmuseum has a fascinating collection of historical nautical items, including a replica of the 18th-century cargo ship Amsterdam. The building was founded in 1656 as a storehouse for the Admiralty in Amsterdam.

title: Foam Photography Museum Amsterdam Tickets
description: This building on the Keizersgracht was originally built in 1685. In the 19th century it was already in use as a museum. First by local Amsterdam artists, it's currently Amsterdam's renowned Photography Museum.

title: Diamond Museum Tickets
description: The Diamond Museum is Amsterdam's sparkliest attraction, plunging you into the history of the city's diamond trade and showcasing world-famous diamonds from all over the globe.

title: Amsterdam Museum Tickets
description: The Amsterdam Museum tells the story of the Dutch capital, from the Middle Ages through the 17th century, and right up to modern times. When it opened its doors in 1926 it was located in the Waag at the Nieuwmarkt. In 1975 the museum moved to its current location, just off the Kalverstraat, a building that was originally a municipal orphange. The collection is full of photos, artifacts and interactive exhibits.

title: Pancake Boat Amsterdam Tickets
description: The Pancake Boat, or Pannenkoekenboot, is a buffet experience in Amsterdam where guests can eat delicious Dutch pancakes while cruising the IJ. The Pancake Boat docks at Amsterdam NDSM, a brief ferry ride away from Centraal Station.

title: The Amsterdam Dungeon Tickets
description: The Amsterdam Dungeon first opened its doors to the public of Amsterdam in 2006 and has been scaring people ever since. The attraction is located inside an historical church and neo-gothic elements of the architecture date back to 1912. You can even see them in some scenes of the show!

title: House of Bols Tickets
description: The House of Bols is a stylish combo of the brand new and the very old. Genever is the Dutch spirit from which gin evolved, and here you’ll find out everything about Lucas Bols – the world’s oldest distilled spirit brand and their 38 liqueurs.

title: Zaanse Schans Tickets
description: Situated on the picturesque Zaan River, Zaanse Schans is an open-air museum that features six working windmills, historic houses, and craft shops. Amble about its quaint lanes and you'll find yourself understanding just how the Dutch lived (and prospered!) in bygone centuries. All of that as you see windmills hard at work and clogs being made.

title: Museum Of The Canals Tickets
description: In a monumental (and gorgeous!) building on the Herengracht, lies the Museum of the Canals (het Grachtenhuis). In this museum you'll develop a deeper appreciation for the Dutch capital - and the waterways that are such an important part of this city's identity.

title: Hard Rock Cafe Amsterdam Tickets
description: The Hard Rock Cafe Amsterdam is one of the most popular restaurants for visitors to the city. It offers good food and service in a top canal-side location, close to Leidseplein and Vondelpark.

title: The Sloten Windmill Tickets
description: The Sloten Windmill is a functioning draining mill. Known in Dutch as the Molen Van Sloten, it is also the only windmill in Amsterdam which is open to the public on a daily basis.

title: Micropia Tickets
description: Micropia is a museum dedicated to the microscopic life of microbes. It is located beside Amsterdam's ARTIS Zoo. It is located east of the Amstel and is easily accessible by tram, or ten minutes' walk from Waterlooplein metro station.

title: Dutch Resistance Museum Tickets
description: The Dutch Resistance Museum explores the period from 14 May 1940 to 5 May 1945, when the Netherlands was occupied by Nazi Germany. Visitors can learn about the Dutch way of life via a series of exhibitions featuring artifacts, objects, video displays, and more.

title: ARTIS Groote Museum Tickets
description: The museum of big questions. From communicating plants to a competition with a chimpanzee, or a smell tunnel where recognition and emotion alternate. Expect a personal expedition as you criss-cross through the museum.

title: Rembrandts Amsterdam Experience Tickets
description: Prepare to step back to the 17th century with Rembrandt's Amsterdam Experience. This 5D experience uses music, video projections and special effects to transport you back to Amsterdam as it was when Rembrandt was a citizen of the city, showing a reconstruction of Rembrandt's studio on the Rozengracht canal where he created his final masterpieces.

title: Huis Willet-Holthuysen Tickets
description: This house on the Herengracht was built in 1685-87 for then-mayor Jacob Hop. Louisa Willet-Holthuysen, widow of art collector Abraham Willet (1828-1888), vacated the property in 1895, leaving the house and its art collection to the city of Amsterdam.

title: Dining in the dark Amsterdam (Ctaste)
description: Want dinner with a difference? Ctaste has what you're looking for, but it might be hard to see. This unique dining experience takes place in total darkness; there isn't a light to be found!

title: Red Light District Tickets
description: Amsterdam's Red Light District is one of the oldest and most famous areas of the city. Entwined with the city's seafaring past, the Red Light District hosts some of the city's oldest structures built in the traditional Dutch style. Wander the classic cobblestone streets and admire high church towers – including the Oude Kerk – around every corner.

title: Muiderslot Castle Tickets
description: Muiderslot Castle is a defensive castle built in the middle ages, just outside of Amsterdam, North Holland. It is now a museum housing relics of the medieval era, as well as its famous residents like Pieter Corneliszoon Hooft. It is roughly 20 kilometers south east of Amsterdam and can be reached via public transport, or bike, in roughly an hour.

title: Aloha Tickets
description: Aloha is a Hawaiian-themed entertainment complex in Amsterdam featuring a full bowling alley, a glow-in-the-dark minigolf course, a laser tag arena, and a grill restaurant and bar. It's the ideal spot for friends and families looking to enjoy a bit of old-fashioned fun in the Dutch capital.

title: Youseum Tickets
description: Youseum is an immersive museum experience in central Amsterdam. With 15 unique rooms each designed by a diverse collective of artists, the museum puts the visitor at the center of each installation, offering a commentary on the rise of the selfie generation.

title: Coronel Kartracing Tickets
description: Coronel Kartracing is an indoor entertainment complex located in the cute Dutch village of Huizen, a 35-minute drive from Amsterdam. Despite the small size of Huizen, Coronel is anything but! It's home to a huge indoor kart-racing track, the largest indoor laser-tag arena in the Netherlands, an 18-hole, glow-in-the-dark mini-golf course, as well as a number of unique escape rooms. It makes for one of the most fun day trips from Amsterdam.

title: Tropenmuseum Tickets
description: The beautiful and historic building in which the Tropenmuseum is housed is a little out of the main tourist areas. It's in leafy Amsterdam Oost, not far from the Artis Zoo. This museum, dedicated to other cultures and countries, is one of Amsterdam hidden treasures.

title: The BonTon Tour Tickets
description: BonTon Stripclub Amsterdam is the oldest, biggest, and best-rated gentlemen's club that Amsterdam has to offer. It's located right in the heart of Amsterdam, just a 5-minute walk from Leidseplein.

title: Fashion for Good Museum Tickets
description: The Fashion for Good Museum is an interactive fashion museum focused on the future of fashion. The museum tells the stories behind the clothes you wear and how the right choices for those clothes can have a positive impact on people and the environment. The Fashion for Good Museum believes that the fashion industry can and must change, and therefore helps to spread the right knowledge about this with innovating exhibitions that weave the real story of fast fashion.

title: Jewish History Museum Tickets
description: Jewish history runs through the streets and buildings of Amsterdam. Reminders of the holocaust are ever-present, from the queues outside the Anne Frank House to the brass cobblestones serving as memorial plaques outside the homes of Jewish residents lost during the war.

title: Museum Het Schip Tickets
description: Museum Het Schip is located in a social housing complex called The Ship, and is one of the most famous and iconic buildings of the Amsterdam School. It is easy to reach via public transport from all areas of Amsterdam.

title: Coronel Glow Minigolf Tickets
description: Head to Huizen and sample Coronel Glow Minigolf's luminous golfing glory. Put your sporting prowess to the test as you putt your way through wondrous worlds – from the jungle to the north pole – in search of that elusive hole-in-one.

title: Brouwerij De 7 Deugden Tickets
description: Located in the west of Amsterdam, Brouwerij De 7 Deugden is a beer brewery that does things a little bit differently. The brewery goes out of its way to employ staff who live with various disabilities, and this philosophy of bravery and virtue is one that extends to the wide selection of unique beer flavors brewed here too.

title: Royal Coster Diamonds Tickets
description: Royal Coster Diamonds is the oldest diamond polishing factory in the world. Founded in 1840, it still operates to this day, and has handled some of the most famous diamonds in the world – including the Koh i Noor.

title: Coronel Adventure Indoor Klimpark Tickets
description: Ziplines, aerial obstacles, and enough climbing to make you feel like king of the jungle! If you're looking for an adventure that requires some courage, then you'll find it at Coronel Adventure Indoor Klimpark. There are 40 obstacles to tackle and three courses to try out, each more difficult than the last!

title: Museum Tot Zover Tickets
description: How do we deal with death? That question is central to the Tot Zover Museum. How we deal with death says a lot about who we are, our origins and the times we live in. The Tot Zover Museum provides information about funeral rituals and offers reflection on mortality in a broad sense.

title: Once Upon a Time Tickets
description: Located in the Museumplein of Amsterdam, Once Upon a Time occupies a temporary space in the vicinity of the Rijksmuseum, Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum and the concert hall. Once Upon a Time hosts an extensive collection of bronze-gilded clocks from Paris.

title: Q.Zone Lasergame Tickets
description: Are you quick to the draw? You'll need it when you spot the other team at Q.Zone Lasergame! Take on the competition in a game of laser tag and see who comes away with the highest score! There are plenty of walls and props to hide behind while you line up the perfect blaster shot amidst brightly-colored bedlam.

title: The Rembrandt House Museum Tickets
description: There's history in the walls and on the walls. The house itself dates to the Dutch Golden Age of the 1600s, and was situated in one of Amsterdam's most prestigious areas. Rembrandt lived there for almost 20 years once he had established himself as Europe’s most innovative painter.

title: Museumplein Tickets
description: Museumplein is one of the most famous and most beautiful squares in Amsterdam. It is surrounded by historical buildings and is home to some of Amsterdam's most famous museums. You can find the Van Gogh Museum, Rijksmuseum, Stedelijk Museum, and the Concertgebouw all side by side.

title: Johan Cruijff ArenA Tickets
description: Amsterdam's Ajax ArenA is so awesome that they spell it with a capital 'A' at the front and the back of the name.

title: Museum Our Lord in the Attic Tickets
description: This 17th-century canal house has a literal highlight - a miniature, yet fully functional, church hidden in its attic!

title: Henri Willig Store Tickets
description: Henri Willig's cheeses are a global phenomenon. The exclusive baby cheese with the colored packages are an essential part of many supermarkets. Goat cheese, organic cheese and all kinds cow cheeses combined with ingredients such as garlic and chili... Willig's cheeses are unique and you'll find them here!

title: Heinen Delfts Blauw Tickets
description: Heinen Delfts Blauw is a great place to shop for Delft Blue gifts and souvenirs. Apart from the usual tourist wares, you can find some antique and high-end items in the store's upper level.

title: FloriWorld Tickets
description: FloriWorld is an immersive flower-themed visitor attraction in Aalsmeer, a small town 30 minutes' drive from Amsterdam. It's located at the entrance to Aalsmeer's famous flower auction house, which is the largest of its kind in the world. FloriWorld combines the timeless allure and beauty of nature with state-of-the-art technology to provide a multisensory experience that brings visitors on a journey through the botanical wonders of the world.

title: Panoramic tour of Amsterdam and cruise along the canal
description: Discover the 'Venice of the North' with this panoramic boat tour and enjoy a cruise on Amsterdam's canal.From the river boat you will be able to admire the best of Amsterdam from the river. You will have the chance to see the must-see spots of the Dutch capital :Leidse SquareAnne Frank's HouseRembrandt's HouseCity HallDam SquareRijksmuseum...You will enjoy the commentary and anecdotes from your multilingual audioguide and discover Amsterdam's unique charm during the rivier cruise.

title: Guided Walking Tour in the Footsteps of Anne Frank - Amsterdam
description: Discover Amsterdam during this walking tour that traces the footsteps of Anne Frank during WWII.Meet your guide in front of the Jewish HIstory museum to start the tour. For the next 2 hours, you will learn about Anne Frank's life in Amsterdam.Walk through the Jewish quarter, where your guide will tell you about local life during German occupation between 1940 and 1945. You will discover the history of Anne Frank and her diary, along with the Hollandsche Schouwburg monument, the quarter's synagogue, and other historic landmarks. The tour will finish near Anne Frank's house.

title: Canal Cruise: Amsterdam by Night
description: Admire Amsterdam by night on this evening canal cruise, and see the city's magical illuminations.Board a boat as the sun sets and embark on a cruise around the best of Amsterdam and its monuments, including:LeidsepleinAnne Frank's HouseRembrandt's HouseCity HallDam SquareRijksmuseumThe Red Light DistrictAnd more!Discover Amsterdam by boat – one of the best ways to tour the city – as you travel down its famous canals to see its key sites lit up by night.

title: Hop-On Hop-Off Bus Tour of Amsterdam – Day pass
description: Make the most of this 24-hour bus travel pass and discover the best of Amsterdam at your own pace.Thanks to this Amsterdam transport pass, you can hop on and hop off at any of the numerous stops conveniently located near the city's main attractions, including:The Royal PalaceDam SquareThe Westerkerk (Western Church)The Magere Brug (Skinny Bridge)Amsterdam's biggest windmillAmsterdam's main museumsAnd more!Enjoy panoramic views of the Dutch capital from the bus while you discover the history of the city and its monuments thanks to pre-recorded multilingual commentary from an audio guide.

title: Pedal Boat rental in Amsterdam - 1h or 1h30
description: Take a pedal boat ride on the canals of Amsterdam and discover the city in a unique way!  From the rental office next to the Rijksmuseum, you will board a pedal boat and discover Amsterdam on the water for the duration of your choice (1h or 1h30). You'll soon see why Amsterdam's waterways are a UNESCO World Heritage Site: the city is beautiful from the water! Guiding your own pedal boat, you will go at your own pace to observe the architecture of the 17th century houses and even take some pictures.Your pedal boat can accommodate up to 4 people, ideal for sharing with family and friends. Amsterdam is truly the city of cycling!

title: Trip to the Fishing Villages of Volendam and Marken – Leaving from Amsterdam
description: Leave Amsterdam and discover the fishing villages of Volendam and Marken with this coach trip.Set off from the capital and travel through the picturesque villages of North Amsterdam, taking in the beautiful scenery that characterizes the coastal region.This excursion will take you to the historic village of Zaanse Schans, one of the most popular tourist destinations in the Netherlands, where you will be able to admire the many windmills and the traditional wooden houses.When you arrive at the fishing villages of Volendam and Marken, you will have the opportunity to visit the traditional Dutch cheese and wooden clog factories. Both of these quaint fishing villages have preserved their traditional seaside atmosphere and rustic landscapes.To complete the experience, you will benefit from a cheese-making demonstration and a boat trip between Marken and Volendam.Thanks to your multilingual audio-guide commentary, you will be immersed in the history of this picturesque region of the Netherlands and discover the traditional culture of the fishing villages.If you choose the 12-noon departure time (with a supplement) you will be able to benefit from a guided tour of a traditional dress museum.

title: 1-Hour Cruise on the Canals of Amsterdam
description: Discover Amsterdam’s most beautiful monuments from the water on a 1-hour cruise on the city’s canals!Climb aboard a boat and set off to discover the many canals of Amsterdam! During this 1-hour sightseeing tour of the city centre, you can admire the buildings, churches, squares and important landmarks of Amsterdam. An audio guide available in 16 languages will tell you more about the city’s landmarks, including:The Anne Frank House Merchants’ housesThe Magere Brug bridgeThe Westerkerk churchThe old Port of AmsterdamAnd more!In just an hour, you will have discovered Amsterdam from a new angle!

title: Admission to the X-Cold Icebar + 3 Drinks
description: Chill out in Amsterdam's X-Cold Icebar! Enjoy three drinks in this extreme-concept bar that is entirely made of ice. Upon arrival at the bar, you will be given a welcome cocktail as you prepare for the Icebar Xperience. After putting on your thermal clothes and gloves, you will be taken on a 20-minute tour of the Icebar, where the temperature is frozen at a constant -10°C. The Icebar is made entirely from ice. Its bar, seats, walls, sculptures... More than 60 tons of ice have been used to sculpt a truly unique venue. You can also enjoy a 4D experience amid the iceburgs. To complete the refreshing experience, two more drinks will be served to you... in glasses made of ice, of course! Alcohol abuse is dangerous for your health. Please drink responsibly

title: Pizza Cruise in Amsterdam - 1:30h
description: Discover Amsterdam with friends or family on this cruise along the city's canals and enjoy a pizza as you go!The Amsterdam canals are the perfect backdrop for a dinner cruise. You will board the boat, sit back and watch the city's landmarks go by: the Magere Brug, the typical 17th century houses, Westerkerk, Anne Frank's House... Once on the way, you will order the pizza of your choice and the boat will stop to collect your freshly made pizzas. Your pizza comes straight out of the oven, so it will still be hot and full of flavour! Sample menu: Chili Chicken or Californian Vegetarian or Hawaii or Margherita or Pepperoni + 2 drinks of your choiceAt sunset, this cruise for young and old will amaze you with its panoramic view of the city and its original way of visiting Amsterdam along the canals.

title: Amsterdam Canal Cruise & Admission to the Xcold Icebar – Skip-the-line access
description: Discover the 'Venice of the North' on a panoramic tour of Amsterdam's canals followed by a visit to the Xcold Icebar with priority access.Jump on board the riverboat and see the best of Amsterdam from the waters of its canals. You will have the chance to admire the must-see attractions of the Dutch capital, including:Leidse SquareAnne Frank's HouseRembrandt's HouseCity HallDam SquareThe RijksmuseumAnd more!Your multilingual audio guide will provide you with commentary and anecdotes as you discover Amsterdam's unique charm during this canal cruise.After getting off the boat, plunge yourself into the amazing world of the Xcold Icebar, every inch of which is covered in ice. Enjoy the bar's surprisingly warm atmosphere as you discover its different areas and unusal decor: a highly unique and memorable experience!

title: Ticket to the Museum of Prostitution + 1-hour Cruise on the Amsterdam Canals
description: Discover the secret side of the Red Light District with your ticket to Red Light Secrets, the Museum of Prostitution, and enjoy a 1-hour cruise on the Amsterdam canals!As you step into the Red Light Secrets Museum, you will discover what is hidden behind the most famous district in Amsterdam. You will find out the secrets of the district known for its windows with illuminated in red, behind which prostitutes entice and wait for customers. The Museum of Prostitution will tell you all about the history of the Red Light District and the sex industry in Amsterdam. As well as your museum trip, enjoy a 1-hour cruise on the canals of Amsterdam, during which you can admire the city from the water and take in some unique views of Amsterdam!

title: Hard Rock Cafe Amsterdam: Priority Access + Meal Included
description: With your priority-access ticket, you’ll be given the first available table at the Hard Rock Cafe Amsterdam, where you’ll be served a 2 or 3-course meal (starter &/or main + dessert) composed of typical American dishes and accompanied by a soft drink.From the comfort of your table, you’ll be able to admire all kinds of memorabilia and collector items belonging to legendary musicians, including: One of Bob Dylan’s jacketsA musical score by Black SabbathA guitar that belonged to Gene Simmons from KissA hat belonging to Run DMC’s Mc DanielsJohn Lennon’s cigarette holderAnd more!You can also browse the Rock Shop to find souvenirs and collector Hard Rock Cafe t-shirts.

title: Visit the Tulip Gardens at Amsterdam's Keukenhof Park - Transport from Amsterdam included
description: Visit Keukenhof, just an hour from Amsterdam, and stroll around the fabulous flower gardens thanks to your skip-the-line ticket!Your driver will pick you up in central Amsterdam and take you 35 kilometers out to enjoy the beautiful tulip gardens f Keukenhoff.Skip the line thanks to your tickets, and, eqipped with you GPS audioguide, visit the gardens at your own pace! Admire the 20 different floral exhibits that are spread throughout the gardens. People come from around the world to admire the flowers here.The gardens are filled with tulips of all colors, with more than 7 thousand bulbs being planted. This beautiful floral mosaic is only open for 2 months each year. Based on an English garden, Keukenhof is decorated each year in a new and unique way.Admire the ephemeral beauty of the Keukenhof gardens and their tulips, which are known around the world!

title: Amsterdam Festival of Lights Seen from the Canals
description: Enjoy the Amsterdam festival of lights from the canals and explore the city, decorated specially for the occasion!The Festival takes place late November to mid-January and creates a special atmosphere in the city for the year-end festivities. This 1 hour 30 minute cruise will allow you to fully appreciate the illuminations and the lighting effects from the canals.You can also take advantage of the audio guide to find out more about Amsterdam's attractions.

title: 1-Day Bus Trip to Bruges – Leaving from Amsterdam
description: Discover the charm of Bruges, the historic city famous for its traditional lace and delicious chocolates.Set off from Amsterdam and travel to Belgium to discover one of the country's most popular tourist destinations.You will have the opportunity to admire the city's many historical monuments and its canals, which are classified as a UNESCO World Heritage Site.After a half-hour guided tour of the city, you will be given some free time to explore the chocolate and lace boutiques, and to discover Bruges' historic heritage.Experience all the charm and wonders of the 'Venice of the North', before returning to Amsterdam in the early evening.

title: Transfer in a Private Vehicle from Schiphol Airport to Your Hotel in Central Amsterdam
description: Land in Amsterdam with peace of mind and be driven to your hotel by your own personal driver! You will meet your driver in arrivals, after you have collected your luggage. This will ensure you don't waste any time looking for your hotel and can set off straight away to explore the city.
